Mashaba was sacked as Bafana Bafana coach in December. JOHANNESBURG - Former Bafana Bafana coach Shakes Mashaba s application to block the South African Football Association (Safa) from appointing another coach has been dismissed by the Labour Court.Mashaba was seeking reinstatement as head coach after being fired in December for gross misconduct insubordination and violating Safa's communications policy.Mashaba's contract with the association was set to run until the end of the 2018 FIFA World Cup.Shakes Mashaba has seen his bid to return as Bafana Bafana coach denied after the Labour Court dismissed his case against Safa.Presiding Judge Robert La Grange did not provide reasons for his dismissal.Mashaba was fired after being seen to publicly rebuke his Safa bosses and some media following his side's 2-1 victory over Senegal in a World Cup qualifier.The outcome now paves the way for the association to hire a new head coach as soon as the first week of March.The likes of Roberto Mancini, Lothar Matthaus and Hassan Shehata are all vying for the job.